mediaNotes:
Behavior and other notes: An adult male Grasshopper Sparrow (male 2) giving trill songs and calls from a small rock break in a field. He was very close to me and in view most of the time. He was foraging for some of the time and just sitting and looking around for most of the time. This individual was followed carefully until he sang primary song that was recorded in cut 3 (at 9.5 meters). Spectrographic analysis indicates that this is the same bird as that designated as male 2.
This is the first high-quality recording of Grasshopper Sparrow trill song that I know of. Recorder HPF on at 80 Hz, -12 dB/octave.
